    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "15cb0eae_664bbbda",
        "filename": "vpython/application/probe.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 112,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T14:18:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So other comments aside, I think it might be easier to provide the Prober with a modified version of PATH that excludes all VirtualEnv roots. Since you already have this function implemented in \"run.go\", you could just reuse it when calling the Prober and not have to worry about any of this junk. This is a simple and effective way of asserting that no Python paths within the \"vpython\" root will be probed, period.\n\nNow that I think about it, is there any reason not to just prune all \"vpython\" root paths from PATH near the beginning of main() (after Bypass)?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 112,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 112,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "49e61ff20ff6e307dae16d7c0b04660aa32598dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f4940a3b_36f0a101",
        "filename": "vpython/application/probe.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 112,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T17:30:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This code is removing all virtualenv pythons (vpython or not) from PATH. I\u0027m not sure why we need another mechanism to do this? The check wrapper callback seems ideal already...",
      "parentUuid": "15cb0eae_664bbbda",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 112,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 112,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "tag": "autogenerated:gerrit:newPatchSet",
      "revId": "49e61ff20ff6e307dae16d7c0b04660aa32598dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8b06cbad_02aceeeb",
        "filename": "vpython/application/probe.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 112,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T17:49:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s ignoring it in PATH for the purposes of searching; however, I\u0027m proposing something bigger: \"vpython\" *never* wants to scan or use an VirtualEnv directory in PATH.\n\n- Implement \"bin\" directory probing function (see comment below).\n- Implement a function that strips \"bin\" directories from PATH (recommend having it log this fact at debug level).\n- Call this function immediately to modify a.opts.Environ and remove all base subdirectories from PATH: https://chromium.googlesource.com/infra/luci/luci-go/+/b05a9b2d66045edd38f248f72ab47fae2dc1542a/vpython/application/application.go#174\n\nThis will eliminate the need to do anything in this file (since PATH will be pure) and in \"run.go\" (same reason).",
      "parentUuid": "f4940a3b_36f0a101",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 112,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 112,
        "endChar": 32
      },
