    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d269795_02be890f",
        "filename": "vpython/application/probe.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 115,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T17:30:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think I want to create a new exported function for this... there\u0027s no reason to scatter the logic across modules (since nothing else needs this)",
      "parentUuid": "9c867f46_da89cad5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 115,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 115,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "tag": "autogenerated:gerrit:newPatchSet",
      "revId": "49e61ff20ff6e307dae16d7c0b04660aa32598dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "17e12ad0_f2b1c048",
        "filename": "vpython/application/probe.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 115,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T17:49:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The rationale would be that this:\na) presupposes the contents of the VirtualEnv, which is in the domain of the \"venv\" sub-package.\nb) presupposes the behavior of \"virtualenv.py\", which is actually fairly arbitrary.\n\nTBH, we should make this solid by having \"venv.go\" drop its own flag (e.g., \".is_virtualenv_bin\") into the \"bin\" directory that it can then search for, decoupling this check from the actual VirtualEnv implementation details. I don\u0027t think scattering this level of awareness into \"application\" package is healthy.",
      "parentUuid": "3d269795_02be890f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 115,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 115,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "revId": "49e61ff20ff6e307dae16d7c0b04660aa32598dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3ea22250_54ed3168",
        "filename": "vpython/application/probe.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 115,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T18:42:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Like I said before though; I want to strip all virtualenvs, no matter what. \"activate_this.py\" is a well documented part of virtualenvs, so I feel comfortable looking for it. However I\u0027ll do the venv stripping logic in the venv package.",
      "parentUuid": "17e12ad0_f2b1c048",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 115,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 115,
        "endChar": 71
      },
