      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed2505e4_1037e206",
        "filename": "vpython/run.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T14:18:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note that this is inadequate:\n\nvenvRoot \u003d \"/path/to/foobar\"\nbinDir \u003d \"/path/to/foo/qux\"\n\nIn this case, \"HasPrefix\" is true but the asserted case is not. Actually for a number of good reasons, consider:\nvenvRoot \u003d filepath.Clean(venvRoot) + os.PathSeparator\n\nAnd use \"filepath.Clean\" on each pathElem below. This should be pretty solid.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 125,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 128,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "49e61ff20ff6e307dae16d7c0b04660aa32598dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b6431e8e_8d173afb",
        "filename": "vpython/run.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T17:30:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How could this happen? the root should be /path/to/root, and bindir should be /path/to/root/id/bin (as I say in the function comment above)? This is an unexported function\ncalled in exactly one place.",
      "parentUuid": "ed2505e4_1037e206",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 125,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 128,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "tag": "autogenerated:gerrit:newPatchSet",
      "revId": "49e61ff20ff6e307dae16d7c0b04660aa32598dc",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "389530c0_b75fb185",
        "filename": "vpython/run.go",
