      },
      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 1109829
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-19T17:49:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suppose it\u0027s not possible given the inputs. See other comment, though - I think that approach is better and would remove the need to do any of this processing. Let run handle prefixing, and let application handle offering a sane, sanitized PATH.\n\nThe rest of this problem is still needed in the \"!strings.HasPrefix\" below (#133), since PATH is not controlled input and could hit that aforementioned scenario.",
      "parentUuid": "b6431e8e_8d173afb",
